$ OSPP.VBS

`OSPP.VBS` is the *Office Software Protection Platform* script. It enables to configure licensed versions of → Microsoft/Office (incl. → Microsoft/Office/Visio and Project) products.
-
However, this script doesn't work for Microsoft 365 Apps or subscription versions of Project and Visio. Instead, the PowerShell script named `vNextDiag.ps1` should be used.
 
`OSPP.VBS` is found in `→ Windows/dirs/Program-Files-x86/Microsoft-Office/OfficeX`

code {
C:\> → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/_xscript_exe[cscript] ospp.vbs /Option:Value ComputerName User Password
code }

The value of `ComputerName` is a remote computer. Omit to use local computer.

sa:
  The value of `UserOperations` under the registry key `→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/Software/Microsoft/Windows-NT/CurrentVersion/SoftwareProtectionPlatform`
